Frequently Asked Questions for HDFC Bank Limited (NYSE:HDB)
What is HDFC Bank Limited's stock symbol?

HDFC Bank Limited trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "HDB."



How often does HDFC Bank Limited pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for HDFC Bank Limited?

HDFC Bank Limited declared an annual dividend on Wednesday, June 7th. Stockholders of record on Thursday, June 29th will be given a dividend of $0.493 per share on Thursday, June 29th. The ex-dividend date is Tuesday, June 27th.  View HDFC Bank Limited's Dividend History.



How were HDFC Bank Limited's earnings last quarter?

HDFC Bank Limited (NYSE:HDB) posted its quarterly earnings results on Friday, January, 17th. The company reported $0.48 EPS for the quarter. The company earned $2.07 billion during the quarter.  View HDFC Bank Limited's Earnings History.



Who are some of HDFC Bank Limited's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to HDFC Bank Limited include Royal Bank Of Canada (RY), Banco Santander, S.A. (SAN), Toronto Dominion Bank (The) (TD), U.S. Bancorp (USB), Westpac Banking Corporation (WBK), Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group (MTU), Itau Unibanco Banco Holding SA (ITUB), Bank of Nova Scotia (The) (BNS), ING Group, N.V. (ING), Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LYG), Banco Bradesco SA (BBD), PNC Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) (PNC), Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA), Lloyds Banking Group PLC (LLOY), Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group (SMFG), Bank Of Montreal (BMO), Barclays PLC (BCS) and Mizuho Financial Group (MFG).



